    tool_call=ToolCall(
        id='call_53f9d5a534c945f5aaef362a',
        call_id=None,
        name='retrieve_information',
        args='{"prompt":"In {{spacex_s1}}, what does the filing say about the SpaceX Bridge Loan, its terms, maturity, and any covenants? Also, what is the Consolidated Leverage Ratio and how is it calculated?"}',
        parsed_args={
            'prompt': 'In {{spacex_s1}}, what does the filing say about the SpaceX Bridge Loan, its terms, maturity, and any covenants? Also, what is the Consolidated Leverage Ratio and how is it calculated?'
        }
    ),
    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output="Based on the provided filing, here are the details regarding the SpaceX Bridge Loan, its terms, maturity, covenants, and the Consolidated Leverage Ratio:\n\n**Overview of the SpaceX Bridge Loan**\nIn March 2026, SpaceX entered into a new unsecured bridge term loan credit agreement providing for an aggregate principal amount of $20,000 million with a syndicate of lenders, with Goldman Sachs Bank USA acting as the administrative agent. The proceeds from this loan were used to extinguish and pay off legacy debts, specifically the X B-1 Term Loan, X B-3 Term Loan, xAI Fixed Rate Loan, xAI Floating Rate Loan, and the xAI 12.5% Senior Secured Notes. The remaining proceeds were used for general corporate purposes. \n\n**Maturity**\nThe SpaceX Bridge Loan matures on September 2, 2027. The Company has the option to extend the maturity date twice, each time by three months (for a total of six months), reaching a final extended maturity date of March 2, 2028. These extensions are subject to the absence of a continuing default and the payment of an extension fee of 0.25% of the aggregate outstanding principal per extension.\n\n**Terms (Interest Rates, Fees, and Repayment)**\n*   **Interest Rates:** At the Company’s election, interest is charged at a rate per annum equal to either:\n    *   (i) Term SOFR plus an applicable margin ranging from 0.75% to 1.75% (depending on the Company's debt rating), or \n    *   (ii) A base rate equal to the highest of (a) the Federal Funds Rate plus 0.5%, (b) the Prime Rate, (c) Term SOFR plus 1.0%, and (d) 1.0%, plus an applicable margin ranging from 0.00% to 0.75%.\n*   **Duration Fees:** The Company must pay duration fees equal to 0.125% of the outstanding principal on the first anniversary of closing, and 0.25% of the outstanding principal on the fifteen-month anniversary of closing.\n*   **Effective Interest Rate:** As of March 31, 2026, the effective interest rate on outstanding borrowings was 4.58%.\n*   **Prepayment:** The loan may be prepaid at any time, in whole or in part, without premium or penalty.\n*   **Mandatory Repayment:** The Company is required to use an amount equal to the net cash proceeds of certain debt financings to repay amounts outstanding under the Bridge Loan. Additionally, the Company must apply an amount equal to the net proceeds of a qualified initial public offering (IPO) to repay such amounts within six months following receipt of those proceeds.\n*   **Guarantors:** The obligations under the SpaceX Bridge Loan are guaranteed on a joint and several basis by X Corp., X.AI LLC, and CTC Property LLC (each a subsidiary of the Company).\n\n**Covenants**\nThe SpaceX Bridge Loan contains customary events of default and affirmative and negative covenants. These include restrictions on:\n*   Liens\n*   Subsidiary indebtedness\n*   Fundamental changes (including an explicit prohibition on the disposition of Starlink assets and other material businesses outside the consolidated group)\n*   Changes in the nature of the Company’s business\n\nThe sole financial maintenance covenant is the requirement to maintain the Consolidated Leverage Ratio. As of March 31, 2026, the Company was in compliance with all covenants under the loan.\n\n**Consolidated Leverage Ratio and Calculation**\nThe Consolidated Leverage Ratio is the sole financial maintenance covenant required by the SpaceX Bridge Loan. \n\n*   **Calculation:** It is defined as the ratio of consolidated funded indebtedness (net of 85% of unrestricted cash) to Consolidated EBITDA (as defined in the loan agreement).\n*   **Requirement:** The Company is required to maintain a Consolidated Leverage Ratio of no greater than **3.75 to 1.0** as of the end of each fiscal quarter.\n*   **Step-up Provision:** There is a temporary step-up allowed to **4.25 to 1.0** for a period of four fiscal quarters following a qualifying acquisition of at least $1.0 billion.",
        error=None,
        metadata=None,
        done=False,
        success=True
    ),
